description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a radiotherapy physicist to come and join our friendly team here at The Dorset Cancer Centre, Poole Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be involved in all aspects of the radiotherapy physics service including QA and dosimetry, treatment planning, brachytherapy and service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dorset Cancer Centre at Poole Hospital has three linear accelerators (one Varian Truebeam, two Varian Clinac iXs) with a fourth linac (Varian Truebeam) situated at our satellite centre in Dorchester. In addition to this we have two Philips CT scanners and a Gulmay orthovoltage unit. Treatment planning is performed using Eclipse and ProSoma. Brachytherapy has its own dedicated suite where our I125 seed service is performed using the Bard quicklink system and Variseed. Our HDR service for gynaecological cancers is planned using Oncentra Masterplan and prostate HDR is planned using Oncentra prostate. Both HDR treatments are delivered using a Flexitron unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jonny Lee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of Radiotherapy Physics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jonny.lee@poole.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 019 2318&lt;/p&gt;
